The paper proposes an architecture for Visual Question Answering (VQA) which utilizes recurrent layers to generate visual and textual attention. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions that the proposed model enables reasoning relations between several parts of the image and question, which indicates that it involves some level of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions that their model outperforms the first place winner on the VQA 1.0 dataset, which suggests that it involves some level of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
